        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer43146945" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14160767672062741536">Grrrrrr. The details almost don&apos;t matter. The outlines of the story will almost always be the same. Greed and hubris. Alan Greenspan bemoaning excess regulation, even as, and after, things go very wrong because there was little regulation. People paying lip service to ideas of risk. In this particular case, abnormal levels of secrecy because these fellows thought they were extra smart (they were - two of them won the Nobel prize shortly before the fund imploded) and their secret formulas and por</span>
  <span id="freeText14160767672062741536" style="display:none">Grrrrrr. The details almost don't matter. The outlines of the story will almost always be the same. Greed and hubris. Alan Greenspan bemoaning excess regulation, even as, and after, things go very wrong because there was little regulation. People paying lip service to ideas of risk. In this particular case, abnormal levels of secrecy because these fellows thought they were extra smart (they were - two of them won the Nobel prize shortly before the fund imploded) and their secret formulas and portfolio allocations were extra special. On the bright side, nothing actually illegal was done in LTCM's case, and the government didn't bail them out with taxpayer money (the Fed arranged a consortium of Wall Street banks to do the bailout). As things began to head south, many of these schmoes moved assets into their wives' names so they wouldn't lose everything. (Moral: be married?) Even as the terms of the bailout were being negotiated, the schmoes insisted that year-end bonuses be written into the deal. Sound familiar? After the bailout, and the public humiliation and shaming, most of them started up new funds. Ain't America great?</span>
  <a data-text-id="14160767672062741536" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


