<div id="review_91232655" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/91232655" />
    <a title="Sagar Jethani" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2972363-sagar-jethani"><img alt="Sagar Jethani" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1319761895p2/2972363.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/91232655?book_show_action=true">Feb 24, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sagar Jethani" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sagar Jethani" href="/user/show/2972363-sagar-jethani">Sagar Jethani</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2972363-sagar-jethani?shelf=finance">finance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer91232655" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3292031651378875072">Lowenstein crafts a superb narrative around the failure of the immense hedge fund, Long Term Capital Management. The details of the failure are complex, but I found myself returning to the fact that so many factors cited as contributing to the near-collapse of the financial system in 2008 were evident ten years earlier with the demise of LTMC:<br/><br/>* Unregulated shadow banks<br/>* Spiraling complexity of derivatives which few understood<br/>* Over-reliance upon computer models which failed to account for the fa</span>
  <span id="freeText3292031651378875072" style="display:none">Lowenstein crafts a superb narrative around the failure of the immense hedge fund, Long Term Capital Management. The details of the failure are complex, but I found myself returning to the fact that so many factors cited as contributing to the near-collapse of the financial system in 2008 were evident ten years earlier with the demise of LTMC:<br /><br />* Unregulated shadow banks<br />* Spiraling complexity of derivatives which few understood<br />* Over-reliance upon computer models which failed to account for the fact that people behave irrationally<br />* The use of immense leverage to magnify returns-- and render even mild downturns fatal to investors<br />* The utter lunacy of Alan Greenspan's free market radicalism and outright refusal to regulate markets<br /><br />This book should be required reading for anyone interested in plumbing the true origins of the financial crisis of 2008 and its painful aftermath. It is written in a compelling, accessible style that should appeal to readers unfamiliar with financial jargon.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3292031651378875072" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


